## Project Structure

```
client.go           # Main client with functional options
http_client.go      # HTTP layer with retry logic (net/http)
auth.go             # OAuth 2.0 implementation
pagination.go       # Pagination iterator
errors.go           # Error types
<resource>.go       # One file per API resource
types_<model>.go    # Data model structs
docs/               # API documentation per resource
```

## Key Patterns

- All methods take `context.Context` as the first argument
- Uses standard `net/http` (no external HTTP dependency)
- Functional options pattern for client configuration
- Errors use `errors.As()` for type checking
- `json` struct tags for serialization
- Go naming conventions (PascalCase exports)

